<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-03-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 52.</seg></opener>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hall</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-03-10"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 10,
                            1885</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Hall is informed that, while the United States Government is prepared to
                        use its influence in averting a conflict and to promote peace, and deems
                        advisable a voluntary combination of interests of the Central American
                        States, no display of force on the part of any one or more States to coerce
                        the others can be countenanced.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>